
- Requirements:

  - A C++ compiler with C++11 support.
    The following compiler has been tested:
    - GCC 5.3 (Linux x86_64).

  - PortAudio with C++ binding (tested with version v19_20140130).

  - Speech Dispatcher (tested with version 0.8.1).

  - GamaTTS (use the latest version).

- Build (Linux):

  pkg_dir=$PWD
  mkdir ../gama_tts_speech_dispatcher_module-build
  cd ../gama_tts_speech_dispatcher_module-build

  cmake -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release $pkg_dir
  # or
  cmake -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -D LIB_DIR_SUFFIX=64 $pkg_dir

  make

- Install (Linux):

  # Execute as root:
  make install

- Add the following line to /etc/speech-dispatcher/speechd.conf
  or ~/.config/speech-dispatcher/speechd.conf (if it doesn't exist,
  copy the other file):

  AddModule "gama_tts" "sd_gama_tts" "gama_tts.conf"

  - Don't forget to uncomment the line:

    AddModule "dummy"         "sd_dummy"      ""

- If the file ~/.config/speech-dispatcher/speechd.conf exists:

  mkdir -p ~/.config/speech-dispatcher/modules/
  cp /etc/speech-dispatcher/modules/gama_tts.conf ~/.config/speech-dispatcher/modules/

- Edit the file gama_tts.conf if necessary. The variable config_dir_path must
  be set to the path to GamaTTS's data.

- Restart speech-dispatcher:

  killall speech-dispatcher

- Test:

  spd-say -O

  spd-say -o gama_tts 'hello world'
